28. sacro. The poet is musarum sacerdos (111. 1. 3) and is under the protection of Apollo, Bacchus and Mereury. The epithet here has some suggestion of an active meaning: the sacer vates is one who can sacrare, consecrare (‘immortalize’ lv. 8. 27 n.). For the thought ef. Pindar Nem.
